  <reg:title>Freshwater Fish Regulation</reg:title>
  <reg:amsincluded>[Last amended March 30, 2022 by B.C. Reg. 76/2022]</reg:amsincluded>
  <reg:regpitid>261_83_pit</reg:regpitid>
  <reg:content>
    <bcl:section id="d2e29" toc="false">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Interpretation</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>In this regulation, <in:term>fish</in:term> means a freshwater species of</bcl:text>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d2e43">
        <bcl:num>a</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>Order <in:em>Petromyzoniformes</in:em> (lampreys),</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d2e55">
        <bcl:num>b</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>Class <in:em>Osteichthyes</in:em> (bony fishes),</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d2e68">
        <bcl:num>c</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>Class <in:em>Crustacea</in:em> (crustaceans), or</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d2e80">
        <bcl:num>d</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>Class <in:em>Mollusca</in:em></bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
      <bcl:text>and their eggs and juvenile stages but does not include</bcl:text>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d2e94">
        <bcl:num>e</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>goldfish, or</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d2e103">
        <bcl:num>f</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>species of ornamental tropical fishes.</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
      <bcl:hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 145/2004, s. 1.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d2e116">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Offences</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>A person commits an offence where the person</bcl:text>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d2e127">
        <bcl:num>a</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>has in possession,</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d2e136">
        <bcl:num>b</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>transports, or</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d2e146">
        <bcl:num>c</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>traffics in</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
      <bcl:text>live fish unless authorized by a permit or a licence.</bcl:text>
      <bcl:hnote>[am. B.C. Regs. 248/2001; 74/2017, App. 2.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d2e162">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Authorization by permit</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>3</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>A regional manager or a person authorized by a regional manager may issue a permit in accordance with this regulation on the terms and for the period the regional manager or the person authorized by the regional manager specifies authorizing a person to</bcl:text>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d2e173">
        <bcl:num>a</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>possess,</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d2e182">
        <bcl:num>b</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>transport, or</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d2e192">
        <bcl:num>c</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>traffic in</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
      <bcl:text>live fish.</bcl:text>
      <bcl:hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 145/2004, s. 2; am. B.C. Reg. 76/2022, s. 3.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d2e208">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Fee for authorization by permit</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>4</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>The fee for a permit issued under section 3 is $25 and the habitat conservation trust fund surcharge to be paid isÂ $5.</bcl:text>
      <bcl:hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 145/2004, s. 2.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <reg:provisionsnote>[Provisions relevant to the enactment of this regulation: <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96488_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Wildlife Act</in:doc></bcl:link>, R.S.B.C. 1996, c. 488, s. 108 (2) and (3).]</reg:provisionsnote>
